C Language features:
====================

	In 1969 first introduced B-Language by kenThompson.
	B-Langauge is a interpreter.so very slow.
	(line by line error check. show only one error)

	in 1972 introduced C-language by Dennis ritche modified B language.

	C is a Compiler. (Whole program error check. show all the error)


	c is high level programming language.

	high level = user understand ( a-z)

		1) filename.c

	low level = machine understand( binary digits 0's and 1's)

		2) filename.obj

		3) filename.exe	

	c is a case sensitive langague.
	(do not change uppercase/lowercase char's in coding)

	c extension: .c	
	(filename max length should be 8 char's)

	c is a structure oriented programming.
	(order , common format)

	software:
		c:/tc/bin
			tc.exe (or) desktop Tubo c7
	
	simple c program: (format 1)
	==============		
		#include<stdio.h>  // stdio: standard input output
		void main()      // only one main function per pgm. 			
		{	       // open main function	
		printf(".....");   // display info. to output screen.			
			
		}	       // close main function
			       // ;(semi colon) statment finished or end line	
		
	// single comment line (do not show error)
	
	/*
		.......
		.........
		multi comment line 
	*/

	software full screen/normal: alt+enter.

	save: f2
	save as: file-->save as
	compile: alt + f9 or compile menu -->compile
	run        : ctrl + f9 or Run menu --> run
	output screen: alt+f5 or window menu-->user screen.
	
	new window: file-->new
	open:f3 or file-->open
	
	c program code line by line delete: ctrl+y

	c program close: alt+f3
	
	c software close: alt+x or file-->quit.
	
	simple program format 2:
	=====================

	#include<stdio.h>
	#include<conio.h> // console input output:  clrscr, getch (only output screen)
	void main()
	{
		clrscr();  // previous output clear.
		printf("....");
		printf("....");		
		getch();  // wait output for read one char from keyboard.		
	}

	alt+f9 
	cltr+f9
	(no need to press alt+f5)

	simple program 3:
	===============
	#include<stdio.h>
	#include<conio.h> // console input output:  clrscr, getch (only output screen)
	void main()
	{
		clrscr();  // previous output clear.
		printf("\n welcome \t to c language");
		printf("c is a high\b level\0 programming language");		
		getch();  // wait output for read one char from keyboard.		
	}
	
	//Escape Sequence

	\n	- cursor move to new line or next line 
	\t	- cursor move to .5 inches space
	\b	- backspace
	\0	- null char
	\"	- double quotes 
	
	
	
